WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:04.000 --> 00:00:12.000
Place the brace on patient‘s leg. Align the center of hinge at mid patella and midline of A/P.

00:00:12.000 --> 00:00:17.000
Place button of lower Quick Fit Buckle into appropriate keyhole above Buckle Stability Shelf

00:00:17.000 --> 00:00:21.000
and close carefully using the palm of the hand to snap the buckle closed. 

00:00:21.000 --> 00:00:25.000
The button is color matched with an identical blue color in the keyhole for intuitive strap selection.

00:00:25.000 --> 00:00:28.000
Have patient bend knee to 90°

00:00:28.000 --> 00:00:33.000
Place button of upper Quick Fit Buckle into appropriate keyhole and close carefully using the palm of the hand.

00:00:33.000 --> 00:00:40.000
The button is color matched with an identical yellow color in the keyhole for intuitive strap selection.

00:00:40.000 --> 00:01:29.000
Remove alligator clip and trim thigh and calf straps to desired length. Alligator clips should be positioned near the Quick Fit buckles

00:01:29.000 --> 00:01:35.000
Have patient bend leg at 45°and set both CPS to “0”. 

00:01:35.000 --> 00:01:53.000
Peel loose the sleeve hooks and adjust the strap tension starting at the calf.

00:01:53.000 --> 00:02:20.000
Both straps are adjusted correctly when the entire strap has contact with the patient’s leg while not applying any unloading force.

00:02:20.000 --> 00:02:50.000
On both CPS, remove alligator clips and trim to desired length. Alligator clips should be positioned near the sleeve hooks, away from the popliteal region.

